$ Excel: Data validation
@ data validation

Excel's *data validation* feature allows to define rules that limit the values that can be entered in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/cell or → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range].

sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Data/Data-Tools/Data-Validation[Data -> Data Tools -> Data Validation]

  In → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model[Excel's Object Model], data validation rules can be created and managed with a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Validation[`validation` object].

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/formatting/conditional[Conditional formatting]
